					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">To be fair, NOACs are not &quot;awful&quot;. They are infact a very accurate clone of the NES/Famicom hardware. Most we find these days do have the mixed up APU duty cycle setting, and tend to have the cartridge port wired wrong leading to the incorrect sound and compatibility issues. <br /><br />But other than that, they are clones. It's a shame that no one with the ASIC's layout ever bothered to correct these simple bugs and start producing better ASICs. But as it has been said, they are cheap and have no interest in anything other than trying to make money. Quality isn't in their vocabulary.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

