						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">tepples wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">kind of digital output your scaler chip expects.<br /></div>That would be digital RGB or digital YCrCb: a clock signal, one or two digital sync signals, and 15 to 24 digital parallel outputs for raw color.<br /><br />But in practice, you're not going to buy someone else's upscalar. So long as you're building a new PPU core, you may as well do it yourself, whether via a linedoubler or a full framebuffer.</div>

